There had been a further 1 807 cases detected in Hubei, the epicentre of the outbreak, taking the total in the province to 59 989. Most of the new deaths on Monday were in Hubei's provincial capital of Wuhan, where the virus is believed to have originated. Wuhan reported 72 new deaths, down from 76 on Sunday. A total of 1 381 people in Wuhan have now died from the virus. New confirmed cases in Wuhan stood at 1 600, down from 1 690 on Sunday. --Reuters--